# UI microcopy

See also: **`forms/accessibility.mdc`** (labels ≠ headings), **`state/error-handling.mdc`** (empty/error branches), **`api/api-error-routing.mdc`** (form vs toast).  
Audit checklist: [`.cursor/skills/ai-slop-check/`](../../skills/ai-slop-check/SKILL.md) (`catalog.md` § Copy — UI microcopy). Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

**Purpose:** Write copy agents and humans can scan in one pass. Operational tone — not marketing voice inside the product.

## Defaults

| Surface | Rule |
| ------- | ---- |
| **Case** | Sentence case for labels, helpers, descriptions, buttons (product names excepted) |
| **Buttons** | Verb + object: `Save draft`, `Create project`, `Try again` — not `Get started` or `Submit` alone when ambiguous |
| **Errors** | What failed + what to do: `Couldn’t save draft. Check your connection and retry.` |
| **Empty states** | Current situation + one primary action — no pep talk or metaphor |
| **Helpers** | One line max under a simple field; link to docs for long explanations |
| **Placeholders** | Format or example value — never repeat the label |

## Forbidden in product UI

Do **not** ship these patterns (maps to ai-slop catalog IDs):

```tsx
// Bad — em dash in short UI chrome (slop-em-dash-ui)
<Button>Save changes — confirm</Button>

// Bad — vague error, no recovery (slop-vague-error)
toast.error("Oops! Something went wrong");

// Bad — filler CTA (slop-filler-cta)
<Button>Get started</Button>  // on empty project list — say Create project

// Bad — click-here phrasing (slop-click-here)
<p>Click here to upload your file</p>

// Bad — label echo (slop-label-echo, quality-redundant-ux-copy)
<Label>Email</Label>
<Input placeholder="Email" />
<p className="text-muted-foreground">Enter your email address</p>

// Bad — ellipsis on static control (slop-ellipsis-ui)
<Button>Save…</Button>  // when not loading

// Bad — apologetic filler on routine validation (slop-sorry-wall)
<p>We're sorry, but this field is required</p>
// Good
<p>Brand name is required</p>
```

Also avoid: **hype verbs** (`seamless`, `leverage`, `unlock`, `empower`), **anthropomorphic** errors (`Your data is happy`), **exclamation spam** in labels/toasts, **Title Case** on every helper line.

## By surface

### Buttons & links

- Primary action names the outcome: `Delete project`, not `Yes` / `OK` in isolation (use `AlertDialog` title for context).
- Destructive: name the thing being destroyed when space allows.
- Loading: disable + spinner or `Saving…` — ellipsis **only** while pending.
- Links in body copy: link text = destination (`View invoice`), not `Click here`.

### Forms

- Every control has a **visible or sr-only `<Label>`** — see `accessibility.mdc`.
- Inline validation: field name + constraint (`URL must start with https://`).
- API field errors: map server messages; don’t wrap in “Unfortunately…”

### Toasts & banners

- Success: past tense + outcome (`Draft saved`).
- Failure: failure + next step; include support/error id when available.
- One sentence when possible; two max.

### Empty & error panels

Align with `error-handling.mdc` state matrix:

| State | Copy shape |
| ----- | ---------- |
| **Empty** | `No projects yet` + `Create project` button |
| **Error** | What we couldn’t load + `Try again` |
| **Offline** | Factual (`You’re offline`) — see `offline-reconnect.mdc` |

No jokes, mascots, or “Nothing to see here!” unless documented in project `exceptions.md` for ai-slop-check.

## Marketing vs product

Landing pages, pricing, and hero sections → **`marketing-copy.mdc`**.  
In-app chrome, settings, tables, dialogs → **this file**.

## Before shipping new strings

1. Read aloud — if it sounds like a SaaS template, rewrite.
2. Remove em dashes from buttons, labels, and toasts.
3. Check label / placeholder / helper don’t repeat the same words.
4. Optional full audit: `@ai-slop-check` on the touched page.
